<doc id="13143" wikidata="Q855729" url="?curid=13143" title="Generalized mean">
<text>In mathematics, generalised means (or power mean or Hölder mean from Otto Hölder) are a family of functions for aggregating sets of numbers. These include as special cases the Pythagorean means (arithmetic, geometric, and harmonic means).

